Melbourne Zoo orangutan Suma was first diagnosed with arthritis in 2013 . 
  She was initially given daily medication to help relieve the pain . 
  On Thursday she underwent a full health check-up at Melbourne Zoo to assess the progress of her condition . 
  Surgeons anaesthetised Suma and took X-rays of her hips and ankles . 
  They also gave her a steroid injection which will reduce her pain . 
 